chanisms of state welfare work. It is a book essential to those interested in how forces unassimilable to conventional economy come to matter in issues of labor, stress, and welfare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBurn out (Psychology)zFinland. 0aBurn out (Psychology). 0aEmployeesxMental healthzFinland. 0aJob stresszFinland. 0aJob stress. 0aWork environmentxPsychological aspects. 0aWork environmentzFinlandxPsychological aspects. 4aLABOR HISTORY. 4aWEST EUROPEAN HISTORY. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Physical.2bisacsh  astress and burnout in Finland, Nordic welfare, occupational burnout in Europe, European labor and burnout,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501768095?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501768095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501768095/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023